<h3><span id="Central_Zone_.28Madhya_or_Hindi.29"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Central_Zone_(Madhya_or_Hindi)">Central Zone (Madhya <i>or</i> Hindi)</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Indo-Aryan_languages&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Central Zone (Madhya or Hindi)">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Hindi_Indoarisch.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Hindi_Indoarisch.png/220px-Hindi_Indoarisch.png" decoding="async" width="220" height="231" class="thumbimage" srcset="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Hindi_Indoarisch.png/330px-Hindi_Indoarisch.png 1.5x, http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Hindi_Indoarisch.png/440px-Hindi_Indoarisch.png 2x" data-file-width="877" data-file-height="919" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Hindi_Indoarisch.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Indic, Central Zone</div></div></div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindi_languages" class="mw-redirect" title="Hindi languages">Hindi languages</a></div>
<dl><dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parya_language" title="Parya language"><b>Parya</b></a> - 4,000 speakers</dt>
<dt>Western Hindi</dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindustani_language" title="Hindustani language">Hindustani</a> (including <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindi" title="Hindi">Standard Hindi</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu" title="Urdu">Standard Urdu</a>) - 250 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Braj_Bhasha" title="Braj Bhasha">Braj</a> - 21 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haryanvi_language" title="Haryanvi language">Haryanvi</a> - 8 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bundeli_language" title="Bundeli language">Bundeli</a> - 3.1 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kannauji_language" title="Kannauji language">Kannauji</a> - 9.5 million speakers</li></ul></dd></dl>
<dl><dt>Eastern Hindi</dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Awadhi_language" title="Awadhi language">Awadhi</a> - 3.5 million speakers
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiji_Hindi" title="Fiji Hindi">Fiji Hindi</a> - 460,000 speakers</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bagheli_language" title="Bagheli language">Bagheli</a> - 8.4 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chhattisgarhi_language" title="Chhattisgarhi language">Chhattisgarhi</a> - 18 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgujia_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Surgujia language">Surgujia</a> - 1.7 million</li></ul></dd></dl>
<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parya" class="mw-redirect" title="Parya">Parya</a> historically belonged to the Central Zone but lost intelligibility with other languages of the group due to geographic distance and numerous grammatical and lexical innovations.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Eastern_Zone">Eastern Zone</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Indo-Aryan_languages&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Eastern Zone">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>These languages derive from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magadhi_Prakrit" title="Magadhi Prakrit">Magadhi Prakrit</a>.
</p><p><b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bihari_languages" title="Bihari languages">Bihari languages</a></b>
</p>
<dl><dt>Kuswaric (unclassified)<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="Old_Indic#cite_note-13">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danwar_language" title="Danwar language">Danwar</a> - 46,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bote-Darai_language" title="Bote-Darai language">Bote-Darai</a> - 20,000 speakers</li></ul></dd></dl>
<dl><dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tharu_languages" title="Tharu languages">Tharu</a> - 1.9 million speakers</dt>
<dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Majhi_language" title="Majhi language">Majhi</a> - 46,120 speakers</dt>
<dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kurmali_language" title="Kurmali language">Kurmali</a> - 556,089 speakers</dt>
<dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surjapuri_language" title="Surjapuri language">Surjapuri</a> - 2,256,228 speakers</dt>
<dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhojpuri_language" title="Bhojpuri language">Bhojpuri</a> - 51 million speakers</dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caribbean_Hindustani" title="Caribbean Hindustani">Caribbean Hindustani</a> - 166,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sadri_language" title="Sadri language">Sadri (Nagpuri)</a> - 5.1 million speakers</li></ul></dd></dl>
<dl><dt></dt>
<dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magahi_language" title="Magahi language">Magahi</a> - 20 million speakers</dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khortha_language" title="Khortha language">Khortha</a> - 8.04 million speakers</li></ul></dd></dl>
<dl><dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maithili_language" title="Maithili language">Maithili</a> - 33.9 million speakers</dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angika" title="Angika">Angkika</a> - 743,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bajjika" title="Bajjika">Bajjika</a> - 12 million speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musasa_language" title="Musasa language">Musasa</a> - 50,000 speakers</li>
<li>Madhur</li>
<li>Jolaha</li>
<li>Kisan</li>
<li>Khortha</li></ul></dd></dl>
<p><b>Odia-Halbic</b>
</p>
<dl><dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odia_language" title="Odia language">Odia</a> - 34 million speakers</dt>
