<dl><dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halbic_languages" title="Halbic languages">Halbic</a></dt>
<dd>
<ul><li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halbi_language" title="Halbi language">Halbi</a> - 766,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhatri_language" title="Bhatri language">Bhatri</a> - 334,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamar_language" title="Kamar language">Kamar</a> - 40,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirgan_language" title="Mirgan language">Mirgan</a> - 60,000 speakers</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nahari_language" title="Nahari language">Nahari</a> - 20,000 speakers</li></ul></dd></dl>
<p><b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bengali%E2%80%93Assamese_languages" title="Bengali–Assamese languages">Bengali–Assamese (বাংলা-অসমীয়া)</a></b>
</p>
<dl><dt><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assamese_language" title="Assamese language">Assamese (অসমীয়া)</a> - 15 million speakers</dt>
