<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20150402100935/https://www.iranica.com/articles/gypsy-ii">"Archived copy"</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.iranica.com/articles/gypsy-ii">the original</a> on 2 April 2015<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">25 March</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranica.com%2Farticles%2Fgypsy-ii&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIndo-Aryan+languages" class="Z3988"></span><span class="cs1-maint citation-comment">CS1 maint: archived copy as title (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:CS1_maint:_archived_copy_as_title" title="Category:CS1 maint: archived copy as title">link</a>)</span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/> Encyclopedia Iranica</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-29">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ethnologue.com/subgroups/romani">"Romani (subgroup)"</a>. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SIL_International" title="SIL International">SIL International</a>. n.d<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">15 September</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Romani+%28subgroup%29&amp;rft.pub=SIL+International&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ethnologue.com%2Fsubgroups%2Fromani&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AIndo-Aryan+languages" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Old_Indic#CITEREFMasica1991">Masica (1991</a>:94–95)</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In Sanskrit, probably /cɕ/ is a more correct representation. Sometimes, only for representation, /c/ is also used.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Some Bengali dialects too have this system, but with /ts/. See below Dhaka and Rajshahi dialects.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-33">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Old_Indic#CITEREFMasica1991">Masica (1991</a>:95–96)</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEMasica199123–27-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Old_Indic#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMasica199123–27_34-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="Old_Indic#CITEREFMasica1991">Masica 1991</a>, pp.&#160;23–27.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
